The evidence with the title 'Potential court pick faced dilemma at Harvard - The New York Times ' says May 6, 2010  ... As Harvard Law School dean, Elena Kagan struggled with how far to go in opposing military recruiters on campus.  ... Her management of the recruiting dispute shows her to have been, above all, a pragmatist, asserting her principles but all the while following the law, so that Harvard never lost its financing. 
